/ we will install jenkins  as a container
docker pull jenkins/jenkins:lts / pulling jenkins latest image

/ Run Jenkins on a specific port 8080 You also need to map a volume for Jenkins data to persist between restarts.

docker run -d \
  --name jenkins \
  -p 8080:8080 \ // if you had any issue try changing port to 8081:8080
  -p 50000:50000 \
  -v jenkins_home:/var/jenkins_home \
  jenkins/jenkins:lts

docker logs -f jenkins / if you need to check logs when it runs

http://localhost:8080 / access jenkins interface 

On the first login, youâ€™ll need an admin password

docker exec -it jenkins cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword


